369 (j) Ethics officer.
370 (1) There is hereby created as a position an ethics officer for Clayton County. The ethics
371 officer may be an employee of the county or an independent contractor. The ethics
372 officer must be an active member of the State Bar of Georgia in good standing with five
373 years' experience in the practice of law. The ethics officer shall be appointed by a
374 majority of the members of the board of ethics, subject to confirmation by a majority of
375 the board of commissioners, for a period not to exceed six years. Removal of the ethics
376 officer before the expiration of the designated term shall be for cause by a majority vote
377 of the members of the board of ethics. The ethics officer need not be a resident of the
378 county at the time of his or her appointment, but he or she shall reside in Clayton County
379 within six months of such appointment and continue to reside therein throughout such
380 appointment.
381 (2) The ethics officer shall not be involved in partisan or nonpartisan political activities
382 or the political affairs of Clayton County.
